        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 29 at 6:37PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking intensifying showers with
isolated embedded thunderstorms 14 miles northwest of Dillon, moving
northeast at 15 mph. A transition to snow is expected as these
showers continue to intensify this evening with locally intense
snowfall rates likely beneath stronger cells.

HAZARD...Locally intense snow with wind gusts up to 30 mph and
isolated lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Intense snowfall rates and gusty winds will create
instances of very low visibility. Heavy snowfall rates will
also lead to quick slushy accumulation on some road
surfaces and slick conditions. These conditions could
impact Homestake Pass to Cardwell Hill on I-90 and portions
of I-15 from Dillon north to Divide.

Locations impacted include...
Melrose, Rimini, Corbin, Dillon, Jackson, Pony, Waterloo, Glen,
Wisdom, Cardwell, Basin, Jefferson City, Bannack State Park,
Whitehall, Grant, Wickes, Boulder, Bannack, Laurin, and Elkhorn State
Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
